label.value: normal pathogen reproductive phenotype within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the pathogen reproductive process within the host is normal (indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal pathogen reproductive phenotype within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype where the pathogen reproductive process within the host is abnormal.

label.value: normal pathogen asexual reproduction within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the pathogen asexual reproduction process, in which new individuals are produced by either a single cell or a group of cells, in the absence of any sexual process is normal (indistinguishable from wild type)(GO:0019954).

label.value: normal pathogen sexual reproduction within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the pathogen sexual reproduction process, in which new individuals are produced by combining the genetic material of two gametes, which may come from two organisms or from a single organism is normal (indistinguishable from wild type) (GO:0019953).

label.value: decreased number of asexual pathogen spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual spores is decreased.

label.value: pathogen host interaction host lesion formation phenotype

definition.value: A phenotype that affects the process of host tissue death causing a host lesion induced by either the pathogen directly killing host tissue (e.g. cell wall degradation), or the host activating its own cell death pathways in defense.
A single species phenotype that affects the cell death within a host.

label.value: increased number of asexual pathogen spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual spores is increased.

label.value: abnormal number of asexual pathogen spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual spores is abnormal

label.value: abnormal pathogen asexual reproduction within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the pathogen asexual reproduction process, in which new individuals are produced by either a single cell or a group of cells, in the absence of any sexual process is abnormal (GO:0019954).
A single species molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a peptidase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: presence of pathogen-associated host defense induced lesions

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion is induced by the host activating its own programmed cell death pathways in defense, is present.
A single organism phenotype that affects the subcellular components in a cell.

label.value: absence of pathogen necrotrophic effector-mediated host programmed cell death

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of a necrotrophic pathogen effector activating the host immune system to trigger programmed cell death is absent.

label.value: presence of effector-independent host hypersensitive response

definition.value: A single species phenotype where the immune system process of host tissue hypersensitive response is present in a pathogen effector-independant manner. (i.e. an alteration within the host is responsible for the activation of the hypersensitive response in the absence of a pathogen).

label.value: absence of pathogen asexual spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the pathogen asexual spores are absent (FAO:0000023).

label.value: abnormal pathogen asexual sporulation within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the process of pathogen asexual sporulation, the formation of spores derived from the products of an asexual cell division, is abnormal (GO:0030436).

label.value: normal pathogen asexual sporulation within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host where the process of pathogen asexual sporulation, the formation of spores derived from the products of an asexual cell division, is normal (GO:0030436).

label.value: presence of pathogen asexual spores within host

definition.value: A pathogen reproductive phenotype within host in which the frequency of occurrence of asexual spores is normal  (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A single species phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain a different number of lipid droplets than normal.
A single organism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size of lipid droplets is decreased.

label.value: presence of pathogen necrotrophic effector-mediated host programmed cell death

definition.value: A phenotype where the process of a necrotrophic pathogen effector activating the host immune system to trigger programmed cell death is present.

A single organism phenotype that affects an intracellular non-membrane-bounded organelle comprising a matrix of coalesced lipids surrounded by a phospholipid monolayer. May include associated proteins.
A single organism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size of lipid droplets is increased.
A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion is present.
A phenotype where the process of host tissue cell death causing a host lesion is absent.

A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways involving those compounds which are formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in many of the chemical changes of compounds that are not necessarily required for growth and maintenance of cells, and are often unique to a taxon. In multicellular organisms secondary metabolism is generally carried out in specific cell types, and may be useful for the organism as a whole. In unicellular organisms, secondary metabolism is often used for the production of antibiotics or for the utilization and acquisition of unusual nutrients.

A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of secondary metabolites, the compounds that are not necessarily required for growth and maintenance of cells, and are often unique to a taxon.

A single organism phenotype that affects the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of toxin, a poisonous compound (typically a protein) that is produced by cells or organisms and that can cause disease when introduced into the body or tissues of an organism.
A single organism phenotype in which the toxin biosynthetic process is normal (i.e. same as the wild type).
A single organism phenotype in which the toxin biosynthetic process is abnormal (i.e. different than the wild type).
Any of the set of observable characteristics of an organism resulting from the interaction of its genotype with the environment.
A single species phenotype that is observed at the level of a population.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype that is observed at the level of an individual cell.
An organism population phenotype in which no organisms in the population are viable.
A single organism cell population phenotype that reflects the proportion of the population that survive and develop normally.

label.value: lipid droplets present in increased numbers

definition.value: A single species phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more lipid droplets than normal.

label.value: lipid droplets present in normal numbers

definition.value: A single species phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain the same number of lipid droplets as normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
